        } else {
            std::cout << "The path is relative." << std::endl;
        }
    } else {
        if (path.substr(0, 2) == "/") {
            std::cout << "The path is absolute." << std::endl;
        } else {
            std::cout << "The path is relative." << std::endl;
        }
    }

    return 0;
}
```

This code prompts the user to input an absolute path and a relative path. It then checks if the path is absolute by checking if it starts with `/` or if it starts with `./`. If it's an absolute path, it prints out that the path is absolute. If it's a relative path, it prints out that the path is relative.

